= stylesheet_link_tag('site_home_page.css')
= stylesheet_link_tag('post_styles.css')

.post
  .post-body
    .post-text  
      %h2.black.text-center
        Lets go step by step
      .whitespace
      .whitespace
      .img-container
        = image_tag(image_url('create_new_welcome_page.png'))
        %p
          Create a new page to start. The title should be your website's name
        

      .img-container  
        = image_tag(image_url('pin_a_sign_up_page.png'))
        %p.black
          Lets add a signup form to the page we have created.

      .img-container
        = image_tag(image_url('create_a_site.png'))
        %p.black
          Since We have not created any site with signup form we will reach to site creation page.

      .img-container 
        = image_tag(image_url('now_we_have_a_site_with_sign_up_form.png'))
        %p.black
          Create a site with sign up form title and description (both are optional)
          
      
      .img-container
        = image_tag(image_url('add_signup_form_questions.png'))
        %p.black
          Go to dashboard and start adding signup form questions.
      
      .img-container  
        = image_tag(image_url('address_question.png'))
        .clearfix
        %p.black
          Lets add a question for asking address.

      
      .img-container
        = image_tag(image_url('the sign_up_form_will_look_like_this.png'))
        %p.black
          Now lets click Preview and see how it look.
      
      
      .img-container
        = image_tag(image_url('go_back_to_welcome_page_and_pin_sign_up_form_there.png'))
        %p.black
          Go back to our page and pin the signup form there
      
      .img-container
        = image_tag(image_url('final_signup_form_will_be_this.png'))
        %p.black
          For a new user, signup form will look like following with mandatory questions name, phone and password for the platform.
      
      .whitespace
      .whitespace
        %h3.black
          Now start preparing our web page
      .whitespace
        
      .img-container  
        = image_tag(image_url('create_a_page_on_our_site.png'))
        %p.black
          Let us create an online back bone for a grocery shop. So we need a survey asking what the user need.
      .img-container
        = image_tag(image_url('create_a_survey.png'))
        %p.black
          Go to survey tab and create a new survey.
        
      .img-container  
        = image_tag(image_url('ask_what_the_user_want.png'))
        %p.black
          After creating survey, go to dashboard. Create few single line questions.
        
      .img-container  
        = image_tag(image_url('the_survey_will_look_like_this.png'))
        %p.black
          You can check the preview on the dashboard.
      .img-container
        = image_tag(image_url('the_site_will_look_like_this.png'))
        %p.black
          Now go to one of the pages you have created and pin the new survey.
      .img-container  
        = image_tag(image_url('we_can_see_response_to_surveys_at_dasdboard.png'))
        %p.black
          You can see survey responses at the dashboard.
      
      .img-container  
        = image_tag(image_url('we_will_see_survey_response_along_with_sign_up_form_response.png'))
        %p.black
          Or on an independent page with all signup form responses
